2. Define the addFavorite() method that takes a string as an argument. This method will be used to add a new favorite name to the list.

3. Define the removeFavorite() method that takes a string as an argument. This method will be used to remove a favorite name from the list.

4. Define the getFavorites() method that returns an array of favorite names. This method will be used to retrieve the list of favorite names.

5. Define the setFavorites() method that takes an array of favorite names as an argument. This method will be used to set the list of favorite names.

Here's the complete FavoritesManager class:

```
<?php

namespace App\Favorites;

use App\Models\User;
use App\Models\Favorite;

class FavoritesManager
{
    protected $user;

    public function __construct(User $user)
    {
        $this->user = $user;
    }

    public function addFavorite(string $name): void
    {
        $favorite = Favorite::create([
            'user_id' => $this->user->id,
            'name' => $name,
        ]);

        $this->user->favorites()->save($favorite);
    }

    public function removeFavorite(string $name): void
    {
        $favorite = $this->user->favorites()->where('name', $name)->first();

        if ($favorite) {
            $favorite->delete();
        }
    }

    public function getFavorites(): array
    {
        return $this->user->favorites()->get()->pluck('name')->toArray();
    }

    public function setFavorites(array $favorites): void
    {
        $this->user->favorites()->delete();

        foreach ($favorites as $favorite) {
            $this->addFavorite($favorite);
        }
    }
}
```

